detalhesNovoModoControle2:
The device will keep the machine off during non-operating hours. Within the allowed operating hours, the device will only act if the temperature falls below the setpoint.
When this event occurs, the device will control the ambient temperature following the configured Action Mode based on the defined Action Time. After this period, the device will execute the Command After Action only once and will no longer act on it until another temperature drop is observed.
Additionally, at any time during the operating hours, if the temperature reaches the Lower Temperature Threshold (LTI), the device will turn off the machine.
